# Blog Voice & Tone — Ryan Realty

## Tone (mandatory for ALL blog content)
- **Honest and transparent**: State facts. When data is ambiguous, say so. Never spin.
- **Authentic**: Write like a knowledgeable neighbor, not a corporate press release.
- **Never pandering**: Do not tell readers what they want to hear. Tell them what they need to know.
- **Optimistic but grounded**: Housing is generally a good long-term asset. Be specific about why, with data.
- **Slightly dry humor**: Occasional wry observations. Never forced, never cheesy.
- **Local authority without arrogance**: Deep knowledge presented humbly. "Here's what we're seeing" not "As the region's top experts."

## Market Analysis Philosophy
- Data-driven: treasury yields → mortgage rates → housing data
- Housing data improves when mortgage rates approach 6%, weakens above 7%
- Track the 10-year Treasury yield (Fed policy drives 65-75% of the relationship)
- Focus on inventory, absorption rates, sold-to-list ratios, and days on market
- Context matters: compare local data to historical norms, not national averages
- Be honest about rate lock effect on supply, but optimistic about long-term fundamentals
- Never name-drop analysts or media personalities — present insights as our own analysis

## Forbidden Words/Phrases
Never use in blog posts:
- "stunning", "nestled", "boasts", "exquisite", "unparalleled", "world-class"
- "don't miss", "won't last", "must see", "once in a lifetime", "exclusive"
- "hot market" (use specific data instead)
- "now is the time to buy/sell" (provide data and let readers decide)
- "dream home" (too subjective)
- "investment opportunity" without supporting data
- No hyphens or colons in user-facing copy/headlines

## Structure
- Every post needs a clear thesis in the first paragraph
- Use data to support claims (specific numbers, not vague references)
- Include local context (what does this mean for Central Oregon specifically?)
- End with actionable takeaway, not a sales pitch
- CTAs should be helpful, not pushy: "Want to see how this affects your neighborhood? Reach out." not "Call us NOW!"

## Content Categories
- Market Updates (local monthly/weekly data)
- Market Analysis (deeper economy, rates, policy analysis)
- Buying Guides (step-by-step, educational)
- Selling Guides (preparation, pricing, staging)
- Community Spotlights (neighborhood deep dives)
- Lifestyle & Living (Central Oregon life)
- Investment & Finance (ROI, rates, strategy)
- First-Time Buyers (beginner-focused)
- Relocation Guides (moving to Central Oregon)
- Home Improvement (renovations, staging, value-add)
- Local News (events, policy, development)

## SEO Requirements
- Every post: unique seo_title (50-60 chars), seo_description (150-160 chars)
- Use long-tail keywords naturally in headings and first paragraph
- Include internal links to relevant pages (/homes-for-sale, /communities, /housing-market, etc.)
- Hero image with descriptive alt text
- Proper heading hierarchy (H2, H3 — never skip levels)
